Here's how to handle each scenario with modern MSTest (3.9+/3.10+):

## 1. Windows-only tests — `[OSCondition]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void WindowsRegistry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\...", "Key", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(value);
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI — `[CICondition]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void GpuRendering_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    // Only runs locally, skipped in CI
    var result = GpuRenderer.Render(scene);
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

## 3. Flaky external API — `[Retry]`

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast(CancellationToken cancellationToken)
{
    var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync("Seattle", cancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
}
```

## 4. Cleanup on failure — `[TestCleanup]` or `IDisposable`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class TempFileTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public TempFileTests()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile_WritesExpectedContent()
    {
        FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.Contains("expected", File.ReadAllText(_tempFile));
    }

    // Runs even if the test fails
    public void Dispose()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `[OSCondition]` and `[CICondition]` require MSTest 3.10+
- `[Retry]` requires MSTest 3.9+ — use only for genuinely flaky external deps, not race conditions
- For cleanup, both `IDisposable` and `[TestCleanup]` guarantee execution even on failure; `IDisposable` is preferred when cleanup is purely sync resource disposal
